sights.name: Heraklion Archaeological Museum
sights.quote: Museum with artifacts from all eras of Cretan history/prehistory, with frescoes, figurines & tombs.

sights.name: Rocca a Mare Fortress
sights.quote: This restored fort built by Venetians in the 16th century has dramatic views & artifacts on display.

sights.name: Minoan Palace of Knossos
sights.quote: Circa-1600-BCE royal palace, reconstructed in the early 1900s & linked to the myth of the Minotaur.

sights.name: Ag. Minás
sights.quote: Prominent Orthodox place of worship built in the 19th century, featuring ornate religious art.

sights.name: Morosini Lions Fountain
sights.quote: Bustling, taverna-lined square centered on a 1600s Venetian fountain with 4 water-gushing lions.

sights.name: Natural History Museum of Crete
sights.quote: Opened in 1981, the natural history museum offers an earthquake simulator & activities for children.
sights.address: Κόλπος Δερματά, Leof. Sofokli Venizelou, Iraklio 712 02, Greece

sights.name: Historical Museum of Crete
sights.quote: This neoclassic building features the art & history of Crete, plus a library & cafe with a terrace.

sights.name: Agios Titos Church
sights.quote: Former 19th-century mosque, now a Greek Orthodox church dedicated to St. Titus.

sights.name: CRETAquarium Thalassókosmos
sights.quote: Modern aquarium featuring 200+ species of marine animals from the Mediterranean, including sharks.

sights.name: Venetian Loggia
sights.quote: Lavish City Hall structure built in the Venetian period with an elegant atrium & hall for events.

sights.name: Venetian City Wall
sights.quote: Preserved defensive city walls dating to the 1400s, with a walkway on top offering scenic views.

sights.name: Lyrarakis Winery
sights.address: Alagni, Arkalochori, 70300, Alagni, Heraklion, Crete 703 00, Greece

sights.name: Skotino Cave
sights.quote: Stunning ancient cave, once used as a Minoan-era house of worship, featuring limestone formations.

sights.name: Aquaworld Aquarium & Reptile Rescue Centre
sights.quote: Longtime facility offering hands-on activities with snakes & other reptiles, plus sea life displays.

sights.name: Dinosauria Park
sights.quote: Whimsical dinosaur park featuring life-size replicas, bones & fossils, plus 3-D films & an eatery.

sights.name: Watercity
sights.quote: Standard water park with slides, a wave pool, 2 children's pools, a jacuzzi & eateries.

sights.name: Phaistos Minoan Palace
sights.quote: Ruins of a Bronze Age archaeological site that includes a Minoan palace & village.

sights.name: Nikos Kazantzakis Museum
sights.quote: Intimate museum highlighting the life of the famous Cretian author with books, photos & artifacts.

sights.name: Diktaion Andron
sights.quote: Cave famous as the birthplace of the mythical god Zeus, with walkways & stairs through its chambers.

sights.quote: Greek mythology-themed park with a maze, mini golf, horseback riding, archery & other attractions.
